<TITLE> Azizul briefs WB team on extra loan needs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 24 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam Tuesdamet a high-powered World Bank team for an assessment of Bangladesh's additional aid need. "The key message [of the government] was to tell them the reasons for additional loan," Azizul told private television station ntv Tuesday afternoon. He said he had told the assessment team about the assistance was needed to maintain growth and poverty reduction acceleration pace and meet the budget deficit . Twenty-five officials of the World Bank headquarters and regional offices taking part in the discussion The closed-door meeting at Radisson Water Garden Hotel had. Bangladesh's GDP growth averaged five percent over last one decade. Poverty reduction rate was 1.8% a year between 2000 and 2005. Azizul explained the government's current move against corruption, change in Public Service Commission, Energy Regulatory Commission (ERC), BTRC and about policy reform in the NCBs and Biman Bangladesh Airlines. "They are not an aid pledging mission, Azizul said of the team. Four sector directors and some other regional officials led by country director Xian Zhu took part in the meeting. bdn
